<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100048379495838></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100048379495838><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100048379495838>RE: quad=kiting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=100048379495838#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=83638><span id=Scholar>Tollen</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>42 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 14th 12:09 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The way I have been quad kiting is Snare 2-4 mobs. Then group them tightly together. So it looks like the mobs are standing on top of each other. Then whip out your aoe dd spell like lightning blast at 34. Then dd the group to death.<br><br>I am currently doing this to tizmacks and cougars in velious.<br><br>Enjoy.<br>&nbsp;<br>Tollen Eyeblinder<br>40th Season Druid<br>League of People<br>Druzzil Ro</td></tr>
