	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm not Tollen, but I'll put a response to your last question here. <br><br>I chose a woodelf because of, really, just preference. I do find, though, that everyone loves female woodelf druids. We are so cute. Every time I am talking to my friends and mention some kindness shown to me I get "you're playing a female woodelf, aren't you?" :) <br><br>It is alot more than the looks, though. (I will say the armor looks for the woodelf females are the coolest IMO) I also liked the natural stats. Up your wisdom and put some in agility. Make sure you have decent CHA, but it will start out fine. Agility I think determines casting time. But you main main one is wis.<br><br>There are plenty of wis items to be found. Don't worry about the ones that neg your cha, btw. Some do. For selling, just unequip them before you go to sell. I always carry a cha booster with me for when I go to sell too :) Eventually, I want a fighting wardrobe and a selling/buying one. Oh, and you will want to unequip it when you start charming and equip you cha booster. You'll sacrifice a little mana and ac, but you'll be getting a pet, which can, if you choose wisely, be much more effective. I kinda look at them as another DoT, atleast right now, while I only have the short-lasting befriend spell. <br><br>Hope you enjoy your druid. Come to quellious. ;)<br><br>Tatiyanna <br>blah blah blah<br>&nbsp;<br>"In waking a tiger, use a very long stick." -Mao Tse-Tung. Did he go to Stonebrunt too?</td></tr>
