	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here's what I have found.<br><br>Halflings: <br>5% exp bonus for race<br>Better stats in melee combat<br>Acolyte quest (footwear with wis is rare)<br>Incredible Newbie Zone in Misty Thicket<br><br>WoodElfs<br>Zone with supper cheap exp items<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;   CB Belts and Bone Chips<br>Lots of people in zone (good or bad)<br>Better Cha (Charming animals and Selling)<br>Tunare Symbol quest (mana less root is incredible)<br><br><br>I am sure I am only scratching the surface. But if these things don't bother you, it doesn't matter which race you choose. Both can easily hit the 200 wis cap. Both are playable and fun. <br><br>But, I have to give massive respect to those people who successfully level a Human or Half-elf druid. No real advantages and lots of people who get in your face about not being a good druid race.<br>&nbsp;<br>Tollen Eyeblinder<br>40th Season Druid<br>League of People<br>Druzzil Ro</td></tr>
